-- Canadian home prices rise in August - Teranet
-- 
-- Fri Sep 12, 2014 09:07AM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, Sept 12 (Reuters) - Canadian home prices rose in August and the pace of 12-month home price appreciation accelerated, the Teranet-National Bank Composite House Price Index showed on Friday.

The index, which measures price changes for repeat sales of single-family homes, showed national home prices rose 0.8 percent last month, exceeding the historical average for August.